                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002"/><desc>A Man standing</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> seated in the center surrounded by four other saints, one of whom is lying on his back before the seat</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#138v" facs="141"/><desc>Three Ethiopian dignitaries each holding a hand <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1071Cross">Cross</ref> in the right hand and a fly swatter in the left hand.  Before them lies a prostrate man</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d5">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#63v #99r #122v #138r" facs="066 101 125 140"/> (line of full stops)
                  </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto) #139r #139v" facs="001 141 142"/>
                    blank, except for scrawls
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#52r" facs="054"/>
                    Two full stops at the head of the line of text indicate the midpoint of the psalms
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#96r #96v" facs="098 099"/>
                    The original hand in <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Chp135"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2000Mazmur, could not check for Chp135</span></title> failed to put the abbreviations for the repeated strophe (“for his lovingkindness endures forever”) and a later hand has added the abbreviation
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#138r" facs="140"/>
                    Scribal prayer for the completion of the manuscript, “Glory and praise to the name of God who helped me to finish in health and peace.”
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    The front cover has a recessed niche in which there was probably a mirror at one time
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#1 #12 #19 #28 #39 #47 #56 #64 #80 #94 #99 #105 #116" facs="003 014 021 030 041 049 058 066 082 096 101 107 118"/>
                    red and blue yarn is sewn into the fore edge to mark content
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 2–12
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <desc>
                      Scribal intervention:
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#37v #42v #62r #63r" facs="040 045 064"/>, etc.);
                      lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#11v" facs="014"/>);
                      lines of text are written in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#104v" facs="105"> f. 104v, line 22</locus>);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#73v" facs="076"/>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <desc>
                    The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (throughout)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
